Key TypeScript Best Practices:

1. Enable strict mode
   - Catches more errors at compile time
   - Better IDE autocomplete

2. Use path aliases
   - Cleaner imports
   - Easy refactoring
   - Better organization

3. noUnusedLocals & noUnusedParameters
   - Prevents dead code
   - Cleaner codebase

4. noImplicitReturns
   - Ensures all code paths return a value
   - Prevents undefined bugs

5. noUncheckedIndexedAccess
   - Array/object access returns T | undefined
   - Prevents runtime errors

6. skipLibCheck
   - Faster compilation
   - Ignore type errors in node_modules

7. isolatedModules
   - Required for Vite
   - Each file can be transpiled independently

